headline: CHIPOTLE ANNOUNCES LEADERSHIP TRANSITIONS
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill (NYSE: CMG) today announced that Ilene Eskenazi, Chief Human Resources Officer (CHRO), has been appointed Chief Legal and Human Resources Officer. Ms. Eskenazi succeeds Roger Theodoredis who has transitioned out of his role of Chief Legal Officer and General Counsel. In addition, Stephanie Perdue, Vice President of Brand Marketing, will serve as Interim Chief Marketing Officer, succeeding Chris Brandt who has transitioned out of his role of President, Chief Brand Officer.

headline: MCD's International Markets Stay Resilient: What's Supporting Comps?
summary: McDonald's leans on resilient international markets as disciplined value, local marketing and scale efficiencies help support comps amid global QSR pressure.

headline: Is Dutch Bros Winning the Coffee Wars With Traffic, Not Pricing?
summary: BROS is standing out by driving same-shop sales with traffic gains, not price hikes, as transactions and digital tools fuel growth.

headline: CHIPOTLE ANNOUNCES FREE DOUBLE PROTEIN OFFER ON TUESDAY, JANUARY 13 TO POWER PROTEIN GOALS
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill (NYSE: CMG) today announced a free double protein offer on bowls, burritos and salads1 on Tuesday, January 13, one of the most popular days to work out.2 With consumers prioritizing active lifestyles in January, Chipotle is curating its menu and offerings to help guests hit their fitness and dietary goals.
